      <p><strong>Individual contributions:</strong> $568,031 (40.0%)</p>
      <p><strong>Small donors (under $200):</strong> $64,413 (4.5%)</p>
      <p class="source-note">Source: <a href="https://www.fec.gov/data/committee/C00764381/?cycle=2024" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">FEC.gov</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="data-card">
      <h3>The Trend</h3>
      <p>PAC dependency has <strong>more than doubled</strong> — from 24% in 2022 to 54% in 2024 to nearly 59% in 2026. Small-dollar donations were <strong>cut by more than half</strong> — from 9.4% to 4.5% to 3.7%. Brown's campaign is becoming <em>more</em> corporate-dependent over time, not less.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

